      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): emit user-visible notice when a turn exhausts its time budget",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen an agent turn exhausts its time budget (`agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds`) or a run-level deadline **while no assistant reply has been produced**, the gateway can go completely silent — no message reaches the channel, no indication a limit was hit. From a user's seat this is indistinguishable from a hung process.\n\nThis is not the prompt/provider timeout case, which already surfaces *\"Request timed out before a response was generated…\"*. It's the **timeout that fires outside a model prompt** — most commonly while a tool is executing on a complex turn. In that case:\n\n- `attempt.timedOut` is `true`, but because `countActiveToolExecutions(...) > 0` the runner also sets `timedOutDuringToolExecution = true`;\n- `timedOutDuringPrompt = timedOut && !timedOutDuringCompaction && !timedOutDuringToolExecution` is therefore `false`, so the existing prompt-timeout notice (`run.ts`, the `timedOutDuringPrompt` branch) is skipped;\n- with no partial assistant text there's no `incompleteTurnText`, so the run falls through to the terminal \"embedded run done\" path, returns `payloads: undefined`, and the reply layer (`auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.ts`) returns silently on the empty payload array.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd one terminal branch in `runEmbeddedAgent` that surfaces a recoverable, user-visible notice when a turn timed out and is about to deliver nothing visible — mirroring the prompt-level timeout copy already emitted from the same function. Because the branch now returns a non-empty payload, it flows through the normal reply-delivery path (gateway-agnostic: Discord, Matrix, etc.) and never reaches the silent `return undefined`.\n\nThe decision is factored into a small pure helper, `resolveTurnBudgetTimeoutNotice(...)`, which returns the notice text only when it is correct to do so and `null` otherwise:\n\n- keyed on **`timedOut`** — distinct from a user cancel (`aborted` / `externalAbort`), so a user-initiated stop never produces the notice;\n- **suppressed** when a visible payload is already being returned (`payloadCount > 0`);\n- **suppressed** for intentionally-silent turns (cron / heartbeat contexts that set `allowEmptyAssistantReplyAsSilent`);\n- **suppressed** when a messaging tool already delivered a reply out-of-band (no double-notify).\n\nA separate copy variant is used for an idle (no-output) model timeout, pointing at the provider-level timeout knob in addition to the agent run ceiling.\n\nNet change is additive: it only produces output where there is currently none.\n\n## Real-behavior proof\n\nDriving the **real** `runEmbeddedAgent` terminal path with a fault-injected timed-out, tool-execution, empty-reply attempt (the exact shape that triggers the silent failure):\n\n**Before (origin/main):**\n```\n[PROOF] result.payloads = undefined\n[PROOF] result.meta.livenessState = blocked\n```\n→ the turn returns no payload; the channel stays silent.\n\n**After (this PR):**\n```\n[PROOF] result.payloads = [{\"text\":\"⚠️ I hit my time budget on this request and stopped before finishing. Ask me to continue, or simplify the request. If this happens often, raise `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds` in your config.\",\"isError\":true}]\n[PROOF] result.meta.livenessState = abandoned\n```\n→ a recoverable notice is delivered through the normal reply path.\n\n(The harness drives `runEmbeddedAgent` via the existing test loader with `makeAttemptResult({ timedOut: true, timedOutDuringToolExecution: true, assistantTexts: [] })`; it is intentionally **not** part of the committed diff — the patch is kept narrow.)\n\n## Tests\n\n- Unit tests for `resolveTurnBudgetTimeoutNotice` covering the full decision matrix (times-out-silently → notice; idle timeout → idle variant; not-timed-out / visible-payload / intentionally-silent / messaging-delivered → `null`).\n- Existing `run.incomplete-turn` suite stays green (118 passed), including the prompt-timeout-races-completion case (visible payload → no notice).\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` and oxlint clean.\n",
        "branch": "fix/emit-user-message-on-turn-timeout",
